title: A trent'anni
body:
A trent’anni

A trent’anni anni arriva il momento di fare i conti con sè stessi.
Di ammettere – senza paura o vergogna – chi siamo davvero, per cosa combattiamo, cosa ci piace.
Ad esempio:
– Kylo Ren
– qualunque live action Disney con le canzoni a palla
– il prossimo film Marvel, vi prego, adesso, grazie

title: Choosing Sides
body:
Steve Rogers * Reader

You’re Tony Stark’s sibling and have chosen to fight alongside Steve Rogers at the airport battle.        

        "Y/n, are you sure you’re up for this? He is your brother.“ You took a deep breath and ran your hand through your hair. Steve Rogers was watching you carefully as you leaned against the car.

        "Tony may be my brother,” you said finally “but he’s wrong. The accords something I can’t agree with so Tony will just have to deal with this. Besides, your friend’s innocent and Tony will never stop to see that.”

        “Thanks for helping us.” Steve said quietly “It means a lot.” You chuckled softly and smiled up at Steve.

        “Well just remember that if this goes wrong and I die, I’m haunting your ass until the end of time.” Steve laughed and moved to stand beside you, prompting you to rest your head on his shoulder. “I’m glad I’m with you Steve.” you whispered.

        “I’m glad you’re with me too Y/n.” he said softly as he wrapped an arm around your waist.

        “Now kiss!” The two of you jumped apart and turned to glare at Sam who was watching the two of you excitedly. Bucky was just smirking at the the two of you causing you to duck your head in embarrassment.

        “Screw you Sam.” you mumbled as he and Bucky got out of the car to greet Clint and the rest of your allies who had just pulled up at the airport.

        “You won’t be saying that when you and Steve end up together.” he said teasingly “And when that happens, I expect you to remember who made it happen.”

        “If we make it out of this alive, yeah I’ll remember.”



        “Your judgement is askew. Your old war buddy killed innocent people yesterday.” Taking a deep breath, you walked out into view and stood beside Steve.

        “And there are five more Super Soldiers just like him Tony.” you said quietly “We can’t let the psychiatrist get to them first.” Tony’s face flickered through a variety of emotions, finally settling into a look of hurt.

        “Why are you doing this Y/n?” he asked frantically “I’m your brother, why are you fighting against me.”

        “Because you’re wrong.” you said, tears trickling down your face “I love you Tony, but this isn’t right. Please, just listen to us. We can talk and figure something out where no one gets hurt.” Tony hesitated and looked down at you. Steve carefully moved to stand in front of you and that’s when Tony’s face hardened and he glared at the two of you.

        “Steve, you’re going to come with us now.” Tony snapped “Y/n, if you choose to stay by his side, you’re going to end up in the same prison they’re sending him too.” You took a deep breath and gently took Steve’s hand in your own.

        “Then so be it.”
